---
import DocumentationLayout from "../layouts/DocumentationLayout.astro";

---

<DocumentationLayout title="Getting Started">
  <section>
    <p class="text-xl mb-6">
      Welcome to Stella - a modern, memory-managed, interpreted programming language designed for flexibility and ease of use.
    </p>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What is Stella?</h2>
    <p>
      Stella is a dynamically-typed programming language that combines the best features of modern programming languages:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 my-4">
      <li>Dynamic typing for flexibility</li>
      <li>Automatic memory management with garbage collection</li>
      <li>First-class functions and closures</li>
      <li>Object-oriented programming with classes and inheritance</li>
      <li>Built-in data structures (arrays and tables)</li>
      <li>Lexical scoping</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Quick Start</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      To get started with Stella, you'll need to:
    </p>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
      <li>Install Stella on your system</li>
      <li>Write your first Stella program</li>
      <li>Run the program using the Stella interpreter</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900 p-4 rounded-md my-6">
      <p class="font-semibold">Ready to dive in?</p>
      <p class="mt-2">
        Head over to the <a href="/getting-started/installation" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 underline">Installation Guide</a> to set up Stella on your system.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocumentationLayout>

